name: TaxAuthority
label: tax authority
definition: regulatory agency that has jurisdiction over the assessment, determination, collection, imposition and other aspects of any tax

name: RegulatoryAgency
label: regulatory agency
definition: public authority or government agency responsible for exercising authority over something in a regulatory or supervisory capacity
explanatoryNote: Typically, a regulatory agency is chartered to protect some constituancy, (e.g., investors in the financial industry), to ensure the fairness and integrity of some market (e.g., the securities market), and fair and safe business practices among the service providers in that market.

name: Examiner
label: examiner
definition: a party empowered as an official representative by a regulatory agency to investigate and review specified documents for accuracy and truthfulness

name: RegulatoryReport
explanatoryNote: Such a report may be needed for licensing, monitoring, taxation, or for other purposes that demonstrate the integrity, fairness, safety, or other capacity of a given industry, organization, or product
label: regulatory report
definition: a report required to support operational transparency that demonstrates compliance with some specification, law, policy, restriction, or other rule specified by a regulatory agency

name: RegulationIdentifier
label: regulation identifier
definition: an identifier associated with a regulation

name: GovernmentIssuedLicense
definition: grant of permission needed to legally perform some task, provide some service, exercise a certain privilege, or pursue some business or occupation
label: government-issued license

name: RegulatoryService
label: regulatory service
definition: a service provided by a regulatory agency, which may include, but not be limited to, examination, monitoring, supervision, testing, or other capabilities required to ensure the integrity, fairness, safety, or other capacity of a given industry, organization, or product

name: RegulatoryCapacity
definition: the capacity of some natural person to regulate some industry, organization, or product by virtue of some certification program on behalf of some regulatory agency
label: regulatory capacity

name: RegulationIdentificationScheme
definition: a scheme for organizing information and allocating identifiers to regulations
label: regulation identification scheme

name: regulates
definition: has regulatory authority over or directs according to rule or law, typically an industry, organization, or product
label: regulates

name: isRegulatedBy
label: is regulated by
definition: indicates a regulatory agency that has regulatory authority for something
